body:
@alexcrichton I believe I've addressed the majority of your comments, modulo a couple things we discussed today.

@nagisa Note that most of the code here is inherited from the existing implementation, not written from scratch. I've put in a round of cleanup, but there are a number of places in the implementation that could be improved. Notably, we should try to use named pipes on windows directly to avoid use of file descriptors here. But the priority at the moment is landing the surface-level APIs; we can improve these implementation details further later on.

That said, I believe I've addressed the concerns you raised.
